I know how MQ works.  Its actually pretty simple in concept.<br>
<br>
The turn in guy needs certain items to obtain a result.  If three people each had one item that the turn guy needed, just make sure the person who needs the result turns in their item last.  <br>
<br>
The shaky part of MQing is knowing if faction is important to the turn in.  For instance, I can't turn in a childs tear for a shammy because my faction with the turn in guy only is at indifferenet, and the turn in guy requires the faction to be ally.<br>
<br>
However, most turn in guys only require indifferent or even dusious.  There are artifical methods to raise your faction to indifferent.   The classic is the hide trick, which can be done by those classess or races that get hide ability.   Its quite simple.   Just goto turn in mob, click on the guy your are giving the item to.  When the item is sitting in the trade window, prior to hitting trade, click your hide skill and con the him.   If he is indifferent your hide was sucessful and click trade.  If not wait and try again.  or just have a 3rd party invis you at that point.<br>
